article.description: — Travis Henson scored 21 points, with seven 3-pointers, and Cal State Bakersfield beat Bethesda 94-43 on Monday night.
article.headline: Henson’s 7 3-pointers lead CSU Bakersfield past Bethesda
article.linkText: Henson’s 7 3-pointers lead CSU Bakersfield past Bethesda
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. -- — Travis Henson scored 21 points, with seven 3-pointers, and Cal State Bakersfield beat Bethesda 94-43 on Monday night. De'Monte Buckingham had 13 points and 11 rebounds for CSU Bakersfield (1-1). Justin Edler-Davis added 12 points. Steve Wooten scored 26 points on 10-of-24 shooting for Bethesda. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25
